│                    SECTION 3: ALLOCATE CONTAINERS - ACTUAL NUMBERS               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

ALLOCATE CONTAINERS -  40 containers max in parallel
1. AM Container  (created first):
   - Resource = 1 GB RAM + 1 core
   - Location = ANY 1 NODES - IT FALIS RM CREATE IT ON ANOTHER NODE ONLY 1 AT TIME
  

2. Task Containers (created by AM negotiating with Scheduler):
   - Resource = 4 GB RAM + 2 cores each
   - Total needed = 800 containers (for 800 blocks)
   - But only 40 can run in parallel
   - Scheduler allocates per wave:

Wave 1:
- Node-1: 8 containers (32 GB RAM + 16 cores used, 32 GB + 0 cores left)
- Node-2: 8 containers (32 GB RAM + 16 cores used, 32 GB + 0 cores left)
- Node-3: 8 containers (32 GB RAM + 16 cores used, 32 GB + 0 cores left) [AM container also here but small]
- Node-4: 8 containers (32 GB RAM + 16 cores used, 32 GB + 0 cores left)
- Node-5: 8 containers (32 GB RAM + 16 cores used, 32 GB + 0 cores left)
Total in Wave 1 = 40 containers processing 40 blocks (5.12 GB)

Wave 2 to Wave 20: Same allocation repeats until all 800 blocks done

