【RESOURCE MANAGER (RM)】 == Master daemon
- Master daemon managing cluster-wide resources and NodeManagers
- Receive job requests and delegate to Scheduler + Application Manager

    【SCHEDULER (under RM)】
    - Allocate containers based on available cluster capacity
    - Give containers in waves, NOT all at once

    【APPLICATION MANAGER (under RM)】
    - Accept job submission and create FIRST container for ApplicationMaster
    - Restart ApplicationMaster if it fails during execution

【APPLICATION MASTER (AM)】
- Runs INSIDE AM Container (1 GB RAM, 1 core typical)
- Negotiate with Scheduler for ALL task containers (mappers/reducers)
- Coordinate task execution, handle failures, and report job status

【NODE MANAGER (NM)】
- Launch containers on assigned node and monitor their resource usage
- Send heartbeat with node status to Resource Manager every few seconds

【CONTAINER - TWO TYPES】

    【TYPE 1: AM CONTAINER (Only 1 per job)】
    - Created FIRST by RM's Application Manager (1 GB RAM, 1 core typical)
    - Runs Application Master process only, NO data processing

    【TYPE 2: TASK CONTAINER (Many per job)】
    - Created LATER by AM negotiating with Scheduler (4 GB RAM, 2 cores typical)
    - Runs actual Mapper or Reducer task, does data work

