【40 CONTAINERS vs 800 BLOCKS - SIMPLE EXAMPLE】

Analogy:
- Blocks = 800 plates of food to serve (each plate = 128 MB)
- Containers = 40 waiters available at same time
- Each waiter takes 1 plate (128 MB) → After finishing, takes next plate
- Each wave processes 5.12 GB (40 plates)
- Takes 20 waves to serve all 800 plates (102.4 GB)

【KEY FORMULA - INTERVIEW MUST KNOW】
Total blocks = 800
Parallel containers = 40
Data per wave = 40 × 128 MB = 5.12 GB
Total waves = 800 ÷ 40 = 20 sequential waves
Each wave processes 40 blocks IN PARALLEL

