【FLOW SUMMARY - 5 STEPS】
Client submits 100 GB file + jar → RM's Application Manager creates AM Container (1 GB, 1 core) →
AM runs inside it → AM negotiates with Scheduler for Task Containers (4 GB, 2 cores each) →
Scheduler gives 40 containers per wave → Each wave processes 40 blocks (5.12 GB) in parallel →
20 waves complete all 800 blocks (100 GB total)

【SUMMARY - START TO END FLOW】
Client → RM → AM Created → AM Registers → AM Requests 800 containers →
Scheduler gives 40 in Wave 1 → 40 Mappers run → Wave 1 done →
Wave 2 to Wave 20 → Reducer Phase → Job Complete
